tasks.description:
CONFIRMED by reading pr_split_15_tui_views.js lines 1601-1610 in session 9. In viewVerificationScreen, the FAIL branch renders:
  lines.push('    Expected: ' + styles.fieldValue().render(equiv.expected));
  lines.push('    Actual:   ' + styles.fieldValue().render(equiv.actual));
BUT verifyEquivalenceDetailed() (pr_split_07_verify.js) returns the object:
  { equivalent: bool, splitTree: string, sourceTree: string, diffFiles: string[], diffSummary: string, error: string }
The fields 'expected' and 'actual' are NEVER set — they are always undefined in JavaScript. This means the FAIL path always renders two blank lines for the tree hashes, giving the user ZERO information about why equivalence verification failed. Additionally: (1) equiv.diffFiles (list of differing files) and equiv.diffSummary are available in the result but never displayed on this screen — the user cannot see which files differ. Fix: (1) Change equiv.expected → equiv.splitTree, equiv.actual → equiv.sourceTree in the viewVerificationScreen FAIL block. (2) After the tree hash lines, add: if (equiv.diffFiles && equiv.diffFiles.length > 0) { lines.push('    Diff files: ' + equiv.diffFiles.join(', ')); } (3) If equiv.diffSummary, add a summary line. (4) Write a test that calls viewVerificationScreen with a mocked state where s.equivalenceResult = { equivalent: false, splitTree: 'abc123', sourceTree: 'def456', diffFiles: ['a.go', 'b.go'] } and asserts both hash values appear in the output and both file names appear.
